Step #1:

$ vi [playbook_script_name].yaml       (or .yml)
    N.B: Always start with --- (03 dash)

Step #2: $ ansible-playbook -i my-inventory [playbook.yml] --syntax-check 	(To check the playbook syntax. No Respone = GOOD)

Step #3: $ ansible-playbook -i my-inventory [playbook.yml] -C	(DRY-RUN)

Step #4: $ ansible-playbook -i my-inventory [playbook.yml]   (TO APPLY THE PLAYBOOK)



-	cp user.yml directory.yml	(copy an existing file to a new file to serve time)
-	vi directoty.yml		(Then modify this current file) 
